PREHEAT broiler. Line baking sheet with foil. COMBINE nectar, cornstarch and nutmeg in a small saucepan; stir until cornstarch is dissolved. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently for 6 to 8 minutes, or until mixture just reaches a boil. Remove from heat. PLACE peach halves cut side up on prepared baking sheet; sprinkle sugar evenly over peach halves. Broil for 5 to 6 minutes or until sugar is caramelized and golden. Transfer to wire rack to cool slightly. TO SERVE, place about 1/4 cup mango coulis on each serving plate. Top with one peach half, caramelized side up. Garnish with mint.